[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]What data do we collect?[/shadow][/outline]
The website collects the folowing data:

Anonymous gameplay data to improve user experience

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]How do we collect your data?[/shadow][/outline]

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]Cookies[/shadow][/outline]
We use cookies to improve the user experience. Cookies store settings such as your username, mute settings, and selected character cosmetics.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]Third-Party Privacy Policies[/shadow][/outline]
Our game and services use third-party providers, which may collect and process data in accordance with their privacy policies:

Colyseus Cloud: Used to manage multiplayer server infrastructure. You can find their privacy policy at https://cloud-prod.colyseus.io/privacy-policy.

GameAnalytics: Used to collect anonymous gameplay data to improve the user experience. Their privacy policy is available at https://gameanalytics.com/trust/privacy/privacy-notice.
We recommend reviewing these third-party privacy policies for detailed information on their data collection practices.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]Analytics[/shadow][/outline]
Anonymous gameplay information is collected via GameAnalytics to improve the user experience. Information about their data collection can be found in their privacy policy.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]User Rights[/shadow][/outline]
Every user is entitled to the following rights:

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to access[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to request copies of your personal data from us. A small fee may be charged for this service.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to rectification[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate. You may also request that incomplete information be completed.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to erasure[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to request that we erase your personal data under certain conditions.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to restrict processing[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal data under certain conditions.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to object to processing[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to object to our processing of your personal data under certain conditions.

[outline color="#ffffff" thickness="0.5"][shadow color="#000000" offsetX="0.2" offsetY="-0.2"]The right to data portability[/shadow][/outline]
 You have the right to request that we transfer your data to another organization or directly to you under certain conditions.

If you would like to exercise any of these rights, please email info@kimchisoupstudios.com with your request.
